2. Tokenize transcription, visualize most frequent words

mt_samples %>%
  unnest_tokens(word, transcription) %>%
  count(word, sort = TRUE) %>%
  top_n(20) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = n, y = fct_reorder(word,n))) +
    geom_col()
Selecting by n

âtheâ âandâ âwasâ were the most used words. The only meaningful word in the top 20 list is âpatientâ, which makes sense. however we still need to remove the stopwords.

3. remove stopwords and numbers

mt_samples %>%
  unnest_tokens(word, transcription) %>%
  count(word, sort = TRUE) %>%
  anti_join(stop_words, by = "word") %>%
  filter(!grepl(pattern = "^[0-9]+$", x = word)) %>%
  top_n(20) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = n, y = fct_reorder(word,n))) +
    geom_col()
Selecting by n

The word âpatientâ is the most frequently used word, followed by left and history.
